---
const items = [
  {
    title: "Wayland compositor",
    body: "Headless compositor and surface streaming are experimental. Some apps will draw fine; others won't. Linux only.",
  },
  {
    title: "macOS / Windows GUI",
    body: "Both platforms multiplex PTYs and stream them to browsers. The GUI compositor is Linux-only and not on the roadmap for either.",
  },
  {
    title: "Hardware encoding",
    body: "NVENC requires the proprietary NVIDIA driver. VA-API needs Intel/AMD with libva. Falls back to software at any time.",
  },
];
---

<section class="border-b border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--bg)]">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-14 max-sm:px-4 max-sm:py-10">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(0,2fr)] lg:items-start">
      <div>
        <div
          class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--accent)]"
        >
          Honest limitations
        </div>
        <h2
          class="mt-3 font-sans text-[clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2rem)] font-bold leading-tight tracking-[-0.02em] text-[var(--bright)]"
        >
          Things to know.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-3 max-w-md text-[14px] leading-relaxed text-[var(--dim)]">
          We'd rather flag what's rough than oversell. blit's PTY core is
          stable; the experimental bits are clearly marked and shipping
          regularly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-3 sm:grid-cols-3">
        {
          items.map(({ title, body }) => (
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--bg-elevated)] p-4">
              <div class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--bright)]">
                {title}
              </div>
              <p class="mt-2 text-[12.5px] leading-relaxed text-[var(--dim)]">{body}</p>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
